TY  - JOUR
AU  - Besley, Timothy
AU  - Coate, Stephen
T1  - An Economic Model of Representative Democracy*
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/02/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355397555136
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 112
IS  - 1
SP  - 85
EP  - 114
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper develops an approach to the study of democratic policy-making where politicians are selected by the people from those citizens who present themselves as candidates for public office. The approach has a number of attractive features. First, it is a conceptualization of a pure form of representative democracy in which government is by, as well as of, the people. Second, the model is analytically tractable, being able to handle multidimensional issue and policy spaces very naturally. Third, it provides a vehicle for answering normative questions about the performance of representative democracy.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355397555136
ER  - 



